summary:
Hey there! I'm Jessica Michelle Hollinger, and I'm all about building relationships and supercharging the sales journey.

Imagine a puzzle – each piece representing a relationship, a strategy, and a shared goal. I specialize in putting this puzzle together, making sure our product aligns perfectly with our customers' needs, driving us forward together.

But here's the secret sauce: I'm not just a sales enthusiast. I have an insatiable hunger for growth and knowledge, diving deep into industry trends. I live by the philosophy that every challenge is a chance to level up – a mindset ingrained in me through my athletic journey and spirit.

Failure? That's just a stepping stone on my path to success. Learning from mistakes fuels my drive to always improve. And speaking of drive, my life's mission is to inspire and empower others to turn their dreams into reality.

Obsessed with entrepreneurship and fascinated by team dynamics, marketing, sales, and product development, I thrive in the dynamic realm where business strategies converge.

I'm always hunting for new ways to maximize positive impact. If you're ready to join forces, let's create a success story that's as thrilling as it is rewarding.

Looking forward to connecting and conquering new horizons together!

profile_positions.description:
I discovered Forager one night as I was exploring the streets of San Jose, my place of living at the time. It had been 4 months since I came out to California and had started my first job. I was loving that, but I was used to always having a side-hustle. I missed the energy of working towards a vision, that constant sense of being on a mission and solving problems.

When I wandered into Forager, it was SJ First Friday and there was a band playing in an old abandoned billiards hall. I saw their business plan flyer laying out and my curiosity got the best of me. As I read, I started to fall in love. Their idea was genius and touched all parts of my interests. 

Beer, food, community, change... 

I approached Heinz and asked if they needed any help with marketing or sales. One thing led to another and next thing I knew I was on the team. Brainstorming, problem-solving and working with passion to make the vision of Forager a reality. 

All though my time with the team was short, the experience was extraordinary and taught me much. I even was able to write one of their first blog posts. 

I had to learn the team dynamic quickly and how to communicate with them effectively. The most challenging and rewarding part though was working to understand the underlying vision of Forager and how to formulate that into words, into pictures, into a blog post, into a brand.

The Purdue Athletes Life Success program (PALS) is a free five-week summer program designed for local underserved Tippecanoe County (IN) children ages 8-14. Now concluding its 13th year, PALS has grown from our first year (2002) enrollment of 200 to 600 youngsters every summer. Our mission is to provide positive growth and development experiences for our children to stay in school, set life goals, make friends, and to dream big. In other words, our mission is to help our children make their lives count. This mission is intentionally consistent with the late Nelson Mandela’s endearing and enduring belief that working on the problem of poverty is nothing less than an act of justice, pure and simple. And even more, that to see and not help children whose lives are diminished diminishes us all.

volunteer_experiences.role: Color Dodgeball for a Cause | Sponsor Outreach
volunteer_experiences.description:
The Color Dodgeball Tournament is an event where students get painted, play dodgeball, and win prizes all for the sake of raising money for Dream Season, the Purdue Cancer Center, and the Scholarship Fund of the National Football Foundation’s Joe Tiller Chapter*. 

Sponsor outreach was my role in this event. I accumulated sponsors by stopping into businesses and/or calling and talking to the business's management. In the end, I gathered 3 sponsors, had a fundraising night, and negotiated a deal for our event's T-shirts.  

*Dream Season is a program that gives a chance to those with special needs to participate in a variety of football camps. 
*The Purdue Cancer Center does a variety of research for multiple types of cancer. 
*The NFF is a foundation that provides scholarships to high school football players who have clearly displayed the qualities of leadership, sportsmanship, competitive zeal, and the drive for academic excellence.
